{{Primary sources|date=November 2010}} {{Infobox organization | name = Eco-Agents | logo = Eco-Agents logo.png | type = NGO | founded_date = 1992 | founder = | location = <!-- this parameter modifies "Headquarters" --> | origins = | key_people = | area_served = [[Norway]] | product = | focus = [[Environmentalism]] | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = 3,000 | subsid = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = | homepage = | dissolved = | footnotes = }}
'''Eco-Agents''' ({{lang-no|Miljøagentene}}) is a member-based [[environmental organization]] for children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miljoagentene.no/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=34 |title=Eco-agents |author=Eco-Agents |accessdate=2008-10-22}}</ref> A subsidiary of the [[Norwegian Society for the Conservation of Nature]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naturvern.no/cgi-bin/naturvern/imaker?id=75656 |title=About Friends of the Earth Norway (FoEN) |author=[[Norwegian Society for the Conservation of Nature]] |accessdate=2008-10-22}}</ref> it has 3000 members.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miljoagentene.no/om-miljoagentene/dette-er-miljoagentene-2.htm |title=Dette er Miljøagentene |author=Eco-Agents |accessdate=2008-10-22 |language=Norwegian |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20110809105106/http://www.miljoagentene.no/om-miljoagentene/dette-er-miljoagentene-2.htm |archivedate=2011-08-09 |df= }}</ref> The three focus issues are conservation of nature, [[global warming]] and consumption.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.miljoagentene.no/om-miljoagentene/dette-er-miljoagentene-4.html |title=Kjernesaker |author=Eco-Agents |accessdate=2008-10-22 |language=Norwegian |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070706070853/http://www.miljoagentene.no/om-miljoagentene/dette-er-miljoagentene-4.html |archivedate=July 6, 2007 }}</ref>
The organization was founded in 1992 as ''Blekkulfs venner'', later ''Blekkulfts miljødetektiver''. In 2006 it changed to the current name, and discontinued its cooperation with the mascot ''[[Blekkulf]]'', a fictional [[octopus]]. The reason was in part to communicate better with older children, and in part because the organization had problems funding the license fees to the creators of the fictional characters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miljojournalen.no/cgi-bin/naturvern/imaker?id=84840 |title=Skiller lag med Blekkulf |author=Christensen, Tor Bjarne |date=2006-05-19 |accessdate=2008-10-22 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>
